VLC(1)                                                                                  General Commands Manual                                                                                 VLC(1)

NNAAMMEE
       vlc, qvlc, svlc, nvlc, rvlc, cvlc - the VLC media player

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       vvllcc [_O_P_T_I_O_N_S] [_I_T_E_M_S]...

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This manual page documents briefly the VVLLCC multimedia player and server.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       VVLLCC follows the usual GNU command line syntax, with long options starting with two dashes (`-').  For a precise description of options, please use "vlc --help".

       The  complete  list of VVLLCC options depends on what plugins are installed because they automatically add their own options. Please use "vlc --longhelp --advanced" for a complete list of avail‚Äê
       able options.

IITTEEMMSS
       VVLLCC recognizes several URL-style items:

       **..mmppgg,, **..vvoobb,, **..aavvii,, **..mmpp33,, **..oogggg,, **..ooppuuss
              Various multimedia file formats

       ddvvdd::////[[<<ddeevviiccee>>]][[@@<<rraaww ddeevviiccee>>]][[##[[<<ttiittllee>>]][[::[[<<cchhaapptteerr>>]][[::<<aannggllee>>]]]]]]
              DVD device (for instance dvd:///dev/dvd). The raw device is optional and must have been prepared beforehand.

       vvccdd::////[[<<ddeevviiccee>>]][[@@{{EE||PP||EE||TT||SS}}[[<<nnuummbbeerr>>]]]]
              VCD device (for instance vcd:///dev/cdrom).

       uuddpp::////[[@@[[<<mmuullttiiccaasstt aaddddrreessss>>]][[::<<llooccaall ppoorrtt>>]]]]
              UDP stream, such as one sent by VLS or another VLC.  Usually "udp://" is enough.

       hhttttpp::////<<sseerrvveerr aaddddrreessss>>[[::<<sseerrvveerr ppoorrtt>>]]//[[<<ffiillee>>]]
              HTTP stream

       rrttsspp::////<<sseerrvveerr aaddddrreessss>>[[::<<sseerrvveerr ppoorrtt>>]]//<<ssttrreeaamm nnaammee>>
              RTSP Video On Demand stream

       vvllcc::////<<ccoommmmaanndd>>
              Execute a playlist command. Commands are: ppaauussee (pause execution of other items), and qquuiitt (close VLC).

EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT VVAARRIIAABBLLEESS
       The following environment variables may affect VLC:

       DDIISSPPLLAAYY
              The X11 display server address.

       hhttttpp__pprrooxxyy
              The HTTP proxy server URL.

       OOSSSSAAUUDDIIOO__DDEEVV
              The default audio output device, used by the OSSv4 output plugin.

       VVLLCC__DDAATTAA__PPAATTHH
              The directory containing VLC run-time data files (e.g. /usr/share/vlc).

       VVLLCC__PPLLUUGGIINN__PPAATTHH
              An extra directory to load VLC plugins from.

       VVLLCC__VVEERRBBOOSSEE
              The level of verbosity for log messages (0: silent, 1: error/info, 2: warning, 3: debug).

       XXDDGG__CCAACCHHEE__DDIIRR XXDDGG__CCOONNFFIIGG__DDIIRR XXDDGG__DDAATTAA__DDIIRR
              The directories to store user cached data, user configuration files and user data files respectively.

       XXDDGG__DDOOCCUUMMEENNTTSS__DDIIRR XXDDGG__DDOOWWNNLLOOAADD__DDIIRR XXDDGG__MMUUSSIICC__DDIIRR XXDDGG__PPIICCTTUURREESS__DDIIRR XXDDGG__VVIIDDEEOO__DDIIRR
              The directories to fetch or store user text files, downloads, music, pictures (i.e. snapshots), and video respectively.

       XXDDGG__SSEESSSSIIOONN__CCOOOOKKIIEE
              The unique identifier of the desktop session, used by the PulseAudio output plugin.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       Online documentation: http://www.videolan.org/doc/

AAUUTTHHOORR
